Package es.upm.pproject.parkingjam.parking_jam.model

Class Level

java.lang.Object
es.upm.pproject.parkingjam.parking_jam.model.Level
public class Level extends Object
Represents a level in the Parking Jam game. A level contains a board, cars, a score, and supports various operations such as moving cars, undoing movements, and resetting the level.

    • undoMovement

      public char[][] undoMovement() throws CannotUndoMovementException, SameMovementException
      Undoes the last movement and restores the previous board state.
      Returns:
      the restored board state.
      Throws:
      CannotUndoMovementException - if there are no movements to undo.
      SameMovementException - if the movement is to the same position.

    • moveCar

      public char[][] moveCar(char car, int length, char way, boolean undo) throws SameMovementException
      Moves the specified car in the specified direction and updates the board state.
      Parameters:
      car - the symbol of the car to move.
      length - the number of tiles to move.
      way - the direction to move ('L', 'R', 'U', 'D').
      undo - boolean indicating whether the movement is a new movement or an undo movement.
      Returns:
      the new board state or null if the move is not possible.
      Throws:
      SameMovementException - if the same movement is repeated.

    • resetLevel

      public void resetLevel()
      Resets the level to its initial state. The score is reset to 0, the board and cars are restored to their default states.

    • checkMovementValidity

      public boolean checkMovementValidity(char carChar, Coordinates newCoordinates, char way) throws SameMovementException
      Checks if the movement of a car to new coordinates in a specified direction is valid.
      Parameters:
      carChar - the symbol of the car to move.
      newCoordinates - the new coordinates for the car.
      way - the direction of the movement ('L', 'R', 'U', 'D').
      Returns:
      true if the movement is valid, false otherwise.
      Throws:
      SameMovementException - if the movement is invalid due to repeating the same movement.
